nodes.text: The Feswe Corridor was an uninhabited star system, located in the Gordian Reach sector of the Outer Rim Territories.
The Corridor was full of closely-packed asteroids, which made navigation difficult. It was named after Feswe, the Rebel Alliance scout who blazed a hyperlane from Ladarra to the Corridor.

The Rebels used the Corridor to smuggle supplies from Feriae Junction to Yavin 4, avoiding the Imperial blockade of the Gordian Reach. Imperials set up two conductor towers in the Corridor in an attempt to freeze a Rebel fleet of Corellian gunships with the Omega Frost, but one of the towers was deactivated by Luke Skywalker before it could harm the fleet.
The Executor was later damaged in the Corridor by the Millennium Falcon after its shields were disabled with a Power gem.
